    "topic": "Compound Interest",
    "subtopic": "Difference between yearly and half-yearly",
    "difficulty": "Medium",
    "question": "What is the difference between the compound interests on Rs. 5000 for 1 year at 4% per annum compounded yearly and half-yearly?",
    "option": {
      "A": "2",
      "B": "3",
      "C": "4",
      "D": "8",
      "E": "None of these"
    },
    "answer": "A",
    "explanation": "Compounded yearly, $CI = 5000(1 + 0.04)^1 - 5000 = 200$. Compounded half-yearly, $CI = 5000(1 + 0.02)^2 - 5000 = 5202 - 5000 = 202$. The difference is $202 - 200 = 2$.",
