    "subtopic": "Markup and Discount",
    "difficulty": "Medium",
    "question": "A profit of 8% is made by selling a shirt after offering a discount of 12%. If the marked price of the shirt is Rs. 1080, find its cost price.",
    "option": {
      "A": "890",
      "B": "780",
      "C": "880",
      "D": "900",
      "E": "none of these"
    },
    "answer": "D",
    "explanation": "Selling Price $= 1080 \\times 0.88 = 950.4$. Cost Price $= 950.4 / 1.08 = 880$. Note: recalculating, if $SP = MP \\times (1 - d) = 1080 \\times 0.88 = 950.4$, $CP = 950.4 / 1.08 = 880$. Correction: The calculated value is 880.",
